{"info": {"author": "Daniel Edgecombe", "author_email": "edgy.edgemond@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "description": "# Mutable Merkle\n[![image](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/mutable_merkle.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/mutable_merkle/)\n[![image](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/mutable_merkle.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/mutable_merkle/)\n[![image](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/mutable_merkle.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/mutable_merkle/)\n![style](https://github.com/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle/workflows/style/badge.svg)\n![tests](https://github.com/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle/workflows/tests/badge.svg)\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle)\n\n``mutable_merkle`` provides a merkle tree with append, update and remove leaf functionality. This \nis intended to support solutions that are not just append only.\n\n```python\n  m1 = mutable_merkle.tree.MerkleTree.new([b\"a\", b\"b\", b\"c\", b\"e\", b\"f\"], hash_type=\"sha256\")\n  m2 = mutable_merkle.tree.MerkleTree.new([b\"a\", b\"b\", b\"c\", b\"d\", b\"e\", b\"f\"], hash_type=\"sha256\")\n  m3 = mutable_merkle.tree.MerkleTree(hash_type=\"sha256\")\n\n  m2.remove_leaf(3)\n  for value in [b\"a\", b\"b\", b\"c\", b\"e\", b\"f\"]:\n      m3.add_leaf(value)\n\n  assert m1.root == m2.root\n  assert m1.root == m3.root\n```\n\n## Serialization\n\nAlong with update and remove leaf functionality, ``mutable_merkle`` has been designed\naround being serializable as well. This supports storage of the merkle tree as well\nas transmission of the proofs.\n\n\n```python\n  mt = mutable_merkle.tree.MerkleTree.new(\n      [b\"a\", b\"b\", b\"c\", b\"d\", b\"e\", b\"f\", b\"g\", b\"h\", b\"i\", b\"j\"],\n      hash_type=hash_type,\n  )\n\n  payload = mt.marshal()\n\n  mt_reload = mutable_merkle.tree.MerkleTree.unmarshal(payload)\n\n  assert mt == mt_reload\n```\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle/", "keywords": "", "license": "Apache-2.0", "maintainer": "Daniel Edgecombe", "maintainer_email": "edgy.edgemond@gmail.com", "name": "mutable-merkle", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mutable-merkle/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mutable-merkle/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle/", "Repository": "https://github.com/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle/"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/mutable-merkle/0.1.1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.5,<4.0", "summary": "A Merkle tree supporting append, update, remove operations.", "version": "0.1.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Mutable Merkle</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/mutable_merkle/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"image\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/70015e345f3c22164bb143e9cb3eeb535d354d58/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f762f6d757461626c655f6d65726b6c652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/mutable_merkle/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"image\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/bad0922b11d220469a2da28c29b603194f19f8d4/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f6c2f6d757461626c655f6d65726b6c652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/mutable_merkle/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"image\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/313c8789926492ca59d8c0d7f2f74b2959fc2a7c/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f707976657273696f6e732f6d757461626c655f6d65726b6c652e737667\"></a>\n<img alt=\"style\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/bedd2abf05217a2ad6ac0d5ebc29368fc04d2d4e/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f45646779456467656d6f6e642f6d757461626c655f6d65726b6c652f776f726b666c6f77732f7374796c652f62616467652e737667\">\n<img alt=\"tests\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/c85971ac08cff5587767e7dddb0f927888cbc3d7/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f45646779456467656d6f6e642f6d757461626c655f6d65726b6c652f776f726b666c6f77732f74657374732f62616467652e737667\">\n<a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/EdgyEdgemond/mutable_merkle\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"codecov\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/281fbe6e6687c8406339f2083f748ccddb21353b/68747470733a2f2f636f6465636f762e696f2f67682f45646779456467656d6f6e642f6d757461626c655f6d65726b6c652f6272616e63682f6d61737465722f67726170682f62616467652e737667\"></a></p>\n<p><code>mutable_merkle</code> provides a merkle tree with append, update and remove leaf functionality. This\nis intended to support solutions that are not just append only.</p>\n<pre>  <span class=\"n\">m1</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mutable_merkle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MerkleTree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"b\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"e\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"f\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span> <span class=\"n\">hash_type</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"sha256\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">m2</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mutable_merkle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MerkleTree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"b\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"d\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"e\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"f\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span> <span class=\"n\">hash_type</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"sha256\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">m3</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mutable_merkle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MerkleTree</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hash_type</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"sha256\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n  <span class=\"n\">m2</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">remove_leaf</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"ow\">in</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"b\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"e\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"f\"</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span>\n      <span class=\"n\">m3</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">add_leaf</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n  <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">m1</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">root</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"n\">m2</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">root</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">m1</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">root</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"n\">m3</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">root</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Serialization</h2>\n<p>Along with update and remove leaf functionality, <code>mutable_merkle</code> has been designed\naround being serializable as well. This supports storage of the merkle tree as well\nas transmission of the proofs.</p>\n<pre>  <span class=\"n\">mt</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mutable_merkle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MerkleTree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"a\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"b\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"c\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"d\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"e\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"f\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"g\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"h\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"i\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"sa\">b</span><span class=\"s2\">\"j\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n      <span class=\"n\">hash_type</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">hash_type</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n  <span class=\"n\">payload</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mt</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">marshal</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n  <span class=\"n\">mt_reload</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mutable_merkle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MerkleTree</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">unmarshal</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">payload</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n  <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">mt</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"n\">mt_reload</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6537730, "releases": {"0.0.13": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ddb7cbcdc22115c50063ac24e2cb6ec8", "sha256": "079912f5599f2a83d1dfcdbbbbe2ea205d305bee9c34c3bc71c716a29ca7f654"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "mutable_merkle-0.0.13.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ddb7cbcdc22115c50063ac24e2cb6ec8", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3748, "upload_time": "2019-05-17T09:55:19", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-05-17T09:55:19.867117Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/9d/39/3876708108808ef2825035f215af01624eb45553aacb63e4abb95fbcac09/mutable_merkle-0.0.13.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.14": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ffea843f0954d86af0a4cb9ae5561f49", "sha256": "d9609b040745b0d102a127e709a6f5b68b6709238752825078f66fa5d234868b"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "mutable_merkle-0.0.14.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ffea843f0954d86af0a4cb9ae5561f49", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3793, "upload_time": "2019-05-1